I move to amend SB632
Of the printed Bill
Page 15 Section Lines 16 1/2
Of the Engrossed Bill
By adding the following language:
"G. Notwithstanding any other provisions of this act to the contrary, in
all actions that may be subject to the jurisdiction of a business court,
no action may proceed unless all parties to the action agree to have the
case heard in the business court. The provisions of this subsection shall
be applicable to plaintiffs, defendants, third party defendants,
intervenors or any other party whether identified at the time the petition
or other pleading is initially filed or identified and becoming a party
after the action is originally filed."
